@@TJvEasterEgg.Active
Description:
if this property is true, the component parse any input from the user and detects the user input. The component doesn't modify the entered keys, it only take a look at them.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvEasterEgg.ControlKeys
Description:
This property is the system keys you want the user to push when entering the string. if you put ssAlt in ControlKeys and "Fun" in Eggid_1541>MAIN, the user'll have to enter alt+Fun to see your easter egg.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvEasterEgg.Egg
Description:
This property is the string you want the user to enter to see the egg. The string is case sensitive.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvEasterEgg.OnEggFound
Description:
This event is fired when the user has successfully entered the keyword with the appropriate control keys. This is where you have to do something fun ;).

